<h1 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Set up a mock server for Trust Anchor</strong></h1>



<p>First, prepare a trust anchor as a mock server with two endpoints.</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Federation Entity Configuration endpoint</li>
</ol>



<p>A HTTP GET request with the path /.well-known/openid-configuration looks like this:</p>



<pre class="wp-block-code"><code class="">GET /.well-known/openid-federation HTTP/1.1
Host: ta.example.com:9091

</code></pre>



<p>And the GET returns JWT, which payload is like below:</p>



<pre class="wp-block-code"><code class="">{
      "exp": 1730322632,
      "iat": 1729322632,
      "iss": "http://ta.example.com",
      "sub": "http://ta.example.com",
      "jwks": {
        "keys": [
          {
 "alg": "RS256",
            "e": "AQAB",
            "kid": "9b26fdf1-595d-48ef-9f56-a47716849255",
            "kty": "RSA",
            "use": "sig",
            "n": "tTlizL_eQMbyOE1V4OXZSzg_2rODbGiYHhnW7ZhtqMJjZdr58NSDDwe5Dp0GzX4ecUaUK1hqX2Gv50tF8bV1qMMVnwDrtf1w8ctcElATf0NPbfgSfRy__t273R6kvJ7SPH5AmiPKA0LRaJSQv53zRwgpxAy2zba588--xdyfv4aYinow5LnaXecuap5l52X0ha7409eTV40shOC84coJTB1BpFECMZjJZ8W8xY1ST9MMyJhmdVLIuHCBKf4ErJImwFDDJO6AIa_kKyA_IbXlArAtU3SntTiNpFSx2t5Bz-rMXdcJTJjEp8ePvQwZPE54hJUV4_QwA79wLGUDbsCeVQ"
